cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MA. 

This paper presents a multi-robot convoying approach that relies on visual detection, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also extensively discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for object detection, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses temporal filtering and tracking-by-detection, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents an empirical comparison of multiple tracker variants, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, and thus falls under the category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
